rComments: Most immunology courses are very information heavy and can be overwhelming if the professor isn't very clear. Ratcliffe's section of this course, while it was short, was perfect. He was extremely clear and explained things clearly and thoroughly. Really enjoyed his lectures, and came out with a good understanding of the material.

Best course I've taken in undergrad. You have to work hard- but if you do, you'll do great and you'll also come out with knowledge about scientific research that puts you way above the rest of your peers out of second year.

Amazingly knowledgeable. VERY friendly and approachable.  He doesn't expect you to know everything. He'll teach you the basics and clarify without making you feel inferior. Honestly, a great person in general.
Very Knowledgeable! The perfect person to ask for clarification!
The best prof in the department, helpful, honest (won't BS you) and very intelligent.
The material is fascinating, he lectures well, and he goes out of his way to accomodate students.  Fair test, too.
fair tests, nice course, no complaints
Good prof. Best immunology prof ever. Degree is hard to get
